{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, Lang shows [30, Theorem 5.5] thatrng C k ⊃ K⊂R d F k (K),where the union is taken over compact subsets of R d. In other words, every flat chain is in the range of C k. The following is the general statement of the Flat Chain Conjecture of Lang [30, p. 716].",
    "Conjecture 2.4.",
    "For every d ∈ N and k∈ N ∪ {0}, if T ∈ D k (R d) has compact support, then C k (T) ∈ F k (K) for some compact K ⊂ R d.We identify T and C k T whenever no confusion can arise.",
    "In particular, we say that a metricd-current T in R d is flat (or that it is a flat chain), if C k (T) is a flat chain.",
    "Remark 2.5."
  ]
}